# CeraLive — x86-64 (Intel N100/N200, AMD) per-family package DELTA
#
# Packages that are x86-SPECIFIC and NOT already carried by either:
#   - shared.list                          (arch-independent runtime), or
#   - v2/manifests/families/x86_64.yaml     (typed BSP + HW-accel arrays)
#
# Consumed by lib/orchestrate.sh only when the resolved board's family == x86_64
# (read_pkg_list shared.list + <family>.delta.list). A missing/empty delta is
# fine — orchestrate.sh skips an absent file and this one carries no active lines.
#
# ============================================================================
# RESULT: this delta is EMPTY.
# ============================================================================
#
# Every x86-specific package is ALREADY captured by the family manifest's typed
# arrays, so duplicating any of them here would violate the "no duplication"
# rule. For traceability, the x86-specific packages and their canonical home are
# listed below as comments (NOT active install lines):
#
#   linux-image-amd64                 -> families/x86_64.yaml: kernel_packages
#   firmware-linux-free               -> families/x86_64.yaml: firmware_packages
#   firmware-linux-nonfree            -> families/x86_64.yaml: firmware_packages
#   intel-microcode                   -> families/x86_64.yaml: firmware_packages
#   gstreamer1.0-vaapi                -> families/x86_64.yaml: hw_accel_gstreamer_plugins
#   intel-media-va-driver-non-free    -> families/x86_64.yaml: hw_accel_gstreamer_plugins
#
# QSV / VA-API element provider (the n100 qsv*/va* elements, D1 caveat 2):
#   gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad is the package that ships the qsvh265enc / qsvh264dec
#   / va* elements the Intel N100 pipelines invoke. It is ALREADY in the SHARED
#   runtime list (shared.list:55, generic "GStreamer core" section — it is not
#   x86-specific; rk3588 installs it too). So it is deliberately NOT repeated in
#   the family manifest's gstreamer_runtime_packages NOR here. The x86 hardware
#   path is enabled by: shared gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad (QSV/VA elements) +
#   gstreamer1.0-vaapi + intel-media-va-driver-non-free (family hw_accel) +
#   gstreamer1.0-libav / gstreamer1.0-plugins-{base,good,ugly} (shared, fallback).
#
# x86 has NO U-Boot blob, NO device-tree package, and NO Armbian BSP — those
# arrays are intentionally empty in the family manifest, so there is nothing to
# delta for them either.
#
# Format: one package per line; `#` comments justify entries.
# (no active package lines — see RESULT above)
